# Epochgram privacy

Effective: 2026-03-20

## Summary

- Epochgram is designed for local-first use.
- Vault content is processed on your device.
- Epochgram Pro uses the network for license validation.

## What data Epochgram processes

### Local (on your device)

- Your vault files and metadata required to build the timeline, search, and similarity features.
- Plugin data stored in your vault config directory (for example, `.obsidian/`), such as indexes, caches, summaries, and settings.

Epochgram does not send your vault content to Epochgram servers.

### Network (Epochgram Pro)

If you use Epochgram Pro license checks, Epochgram may send the following to the license service for validation:

- Email address
- License key
- Basic server-side telemetry necessary for license validation

## On-device AI (Chrome AI Bridge)

When using the Pro AI Bridge, Epochgram starts a local server on `http://127.0.0.1` and opens a local bridge page in Google Chrome. Summary text is processed in Chrome on your device and returned to the plugin.

Chrome may download its built-in model(s) the first time you use these APIs.

## Model and runtime downloads (Similarity)

Similarity features may download embedding and classification models on first use via `@xenova/transformers`. ONNX Runtime Web WASM may also be downloaded depending on your configuration.

